This paper deals with vision-based autonomous driving, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also addresses the issue of domain shift, which is a common problem in robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a framework for end-to-end autonomous driving, which is a topic that falls under systems and control (cs.SY).
